comment: Runner-up in three of her last four starts; rain won't hurt her chance; solid claims

comment: AW win (5f) ten days ago; penalised but still more appealing than most of these
spotlight: Off the mark at the 16th attempt when readily seeing off nine rivals in a similar event at Wolverhampton ten days ago (5f); has a 6lb penalty to shoulder but her recent winning form is a big plus at this level.

comment: Three wins this year, the latest a narrow one at Hamilton; in the mix again up just 2lb
spotlight: Three wins on turf this year, the latest when narrowly seeing off Eternal Sunshine at Hamilton 12 days ago (strong in the betting); 2lb rise shouldn't stop him from going well once again.

comment: First and second in two C&D runs this year; flopped last time but can do better today
spotlight: He has blown hot and cold in 2025, last of 17 in the Great St Wilfrid at Ripon two weeks ago, but his C&D win in May was a fine effort, as was his penultimate second here (both on good ground).

owner: Exors Of The Late Adrian McAlpine
comment: 6f win in Bahrain in January; down the field in three runs back in Britain after a wind op
spotlight: Won a 6f handicap in Bahrain in January; down the field in three runs back in Britain this summer (after a wind operation) and although he dropping down the weights, others appeal more.

spotlight: Gained a deserved victory at York in May (6f, good to firm) and he ran well on his next three starts; failed to fire in the Great St Wilfrid two weeks ago but he was sent off favourite and remains on a dangerous mark.

comment: C&D winner last year; two handicap wins this season, including last time; contender up 3lb
spotlight: C&D maiden winner as a 2yo; two wins in 6f handicaps this year, the latest a Class 4 at Leicester 19 days ago; conditions will suit and a 3lb rise shouldn't handicap him out of things.

comment: Won this last year off 2lb higher; last 3 runs below par but returning cheekpieces a plus
spotlight: Won the corresponding race 12 months ago off a 2lb higher mark; looked booked for another good season when finishing fast for second over 5f here in May; struggled in three runs since but cheekpieces return today and Paul Mulrennan is back on board; big player.

comment: Two-time course winner; good 2nd at Ripon 13 days ago; promising apprentice takes off 5lb
spotlight: Yet to win this year but latest Ripon second was a solid effort; two-time course winner and apprentice's claim useful; each-way shout.

comment: Smart 2yo; quiet this year but he's run okay in deep 3yo handicaps on last two starts
spotlight: Smart 2yo, including third place in the Coventry Stakes; slow start to 2025 but he has run creditably in deep 3yo handicaps on his last two starts; something bigger could be brewing.

comment: C&D winner; ran a cracker at York nine days ago; 3lb well in; should go well
spotlight: Chased home Sir Garfield at Hamilton and then turned in a career best when pipped at the post in a hot 5f fillies' handicap at York's Ebor meeting last week; well beaten over 7f the following day but she can be given a pass for that; 3lb ahead of her mark and has a C&D win on her record; not discounted.

comment: Two Ripon wins last season but struggling in 2025; had another wind op since latest run
spotlight: Won twice at Ripon last season; well short of that level in 2025 and hopes rest on a wind operation, his second, having a positive effect.

comment: On a dangerous mark; type to come good when underfoot conditions deteriorate
spotlight: Unplaced in four runs for new stable this season; down in the weights and didn't run badly at Doncaster five weeks ago (6f, good to soft); might not be one for today but, given his penchant for slow ground, he's one to keep an eye on with a view to the autumn.

comment: Dropping down the weights but others bring more pressing claims
spotlight: Signs of retaining ability this year but last two runs were disappointing and others look stronger.

comment: Non stayer over 7f and 1m2f on last two starts; could still have potential as a sprinter
spotlight: Stayed on to finish fourth of ten in a 6f handicap at Ripon in May; raced freely and failed to get home over 7f next time, or 1m2f when last seen eight weeks ago; not easily fancied at the weights but could have more to offer as a sprinter.

comment: Drops back in trip/grade with Paul Mulrennan booked; still capable of better
spotlight: Down the field in three 6f maidens; no improvement for the step up to 7.4f in a couple of Beverley handicaps this summer; drops in grade with Paul Mulrennan booked; not discounted.

comment: Fourth at this level five weeks ago (7f, AW); needs more dropped back to 6f
spotlight: Showed some pace in a 7f classified event at Newcastle five weeks ago but that was a weak event, even by 0-50 standards; drop in trip might help but improvement is a must.

comment: 6f handicap win in June and several good runs in defeat since; should go well again
spotlight: Made all to win a 6f handicap at Hamilton in June (blinkered first time) and has held his form in defeat since; no obvious reason why he couldn't play a big role at this level.

comment: Low-grade maiden; well beaten on recent stable/seasonal debut; transformation needed
spotlight: Little solid form to her name and she was well beaten on her stable/seasonal debut 12 days ago; might come on for that but far from solid.

comment: Exposed 25-race maiden but third over C&D twice for her new yard this year; e-w shout
spotlight: 25-race maiden but she's only had three starts for this yard and she's finished a close third over C&D in two of them; each-way shout once more.

comment: Two runs this month have seen him tailed off over C&D and then blowing the start latest
spotlight: Should be making a big impact at this level but two runs this month have seen him finish tailed off over C&D and then blowing the start at Southwell; obvious claims if breaking on terms.

comment: Progressed well in nurseries for Karl Burke; absent 350 days but not fully exposed
spotlight: On the up once switched to nurseries last summer, winning at Glorious Goodwood and then placed at both the Ebor meeting and the St Leger meeting; gelded during his 350-day absence; still has potential and he is an interesting contender on his first run for a new stable.

comment: Handicap mark in freefall; carries risk but accessories/drop in grade could spark revival
spotlight: Her first two runs for this stable weren't too bad (both 6f, AW) but she has regressed since; handicap mark in freefall and this represents the weakest race she's contested; a visor returns and a new tongue tie-now added; risky but not impossible.

owner: D Caslin, P Wilcock & M Cantillon
comment: Has won at 6f but better known for 5f exploits; ran well from a poor track position latest
spotlight: Won his maiden over this trip but better known for his exploits at 5f, including a Haydock win off this mark in May; faced a hopeless task as things panned out back at Haydock 19 days ago but he did best of those to race up the middle of the track; the trip is the nagging doubt today.

comment: 100,000euros yearling; Mehmas half-brother to two French scorers; check the betting
spotlight: 100,000euros yearling; Mehmas half-brother to French winners Chiricco (7f/1m) and Ciel De Paris (1m), out of well-related French 8.5f/1m1f scorer; check the betting.

comment: Back on good mark and better signs lately, including at York last week; enters reckoning
spotlight: Former Thirsk Hunt Cup winner who has his lowest mark for over two years and has shown better signs in his recent starts, including fifth of 17 to Bullet Point in valuable 1m handicap at last week's York Ebor meeting; has to enter the reckoning.

comment: Looked really good early but struggled more recently, including for new yard this year
spotlight: Looked a potential superstar early on for Sir Michael Stoute but struggled in two of three runs last year and he's yet to feature for new yard, including when switched to handicap company for the Great St Wilfrid over 6f at Ripon 13 days ago; a refitted hood and first-time tongue-tie needs to have a positive effect.

comment: 150,000gns yearling; by Sea The Moon; yard is 0-6 with 2yos this term
spotlight: 60,000gns foal, 150,000gns yearling; Sea The Moon half-brother to French 6f winner Hedwig, out of Group-placed 6f 2yo scorer (RPR 103); yard is 0-6 with 2yos this term.

comment: Royal Lodge entry who sets the form standard back down in trip; third over C&D on debut
spotlight: Royal Lodge entry; has posted similar RPRs in C&D maiden (third of 11) and Newmarket contest (fourth of five; pulled hard); may settle better back down in trip and sets the form standard.

comment: Pinatubo half-brother to a French winner; powerful yard's 2yo strike-rate is impressive
spotlight: Pinatubo half-brother to French 6f winner Dream Whisper (RPR 92); dam 5f 2yo scorer (99), closely related to 1m4f Group 1 winner Old Persian; powerful yard's 2yo strike-rate is impressive.

comment: 65,000gns (breeze-up) 2yo; by Ulysses out of Listed winner; already gelded
spotlight: 20,000gns foal, 18,000gns yearling, 65,000gns (breeze-up) 2yo; Ulysses sibling to four winners, notably Ice Sprite (1m2f/11.4f; 99); dam 1m4f Listed scorer (108); already gelded.

comment: C&D winner; fine second at Haydock (7f) in July but only fifth at Chester since
spotlight: C&D novice winner on good to soft last summer and added a 7f Lingfield AW handicap in November; just as good in defeat when second of 11 at Haydock (7f, good) in July but faded into fifth when favourite at Chester since.

owner: W G & A G Vestey, E Gerber And P Inglett
comment: 90,000gns yearling; by Teofilo out of half-sister to 7f 2yo Group 1 scorer
spotlight: 90,000gns yearling; Teofilo sibling to three winners, notably Quest For Fun (6f/7f; 96); dam maiden (69) half-sister to 7f 2yo Group 1 scorer Parish Hall; check the betting.

comment: Nicely bred debutant, by Dubawi and first foal of a Group 3 winner for his connections
spotlight: Nicely bred debutant, by Dubawi and first foal of a 7.4f-1m2f winner (including 2yo/Group 3; RPR 115) for his notable connections; both parents scored first time out; commands respect.

comment: Showed promise, albeit without landing a blow, in Doncaster event; may improve
spotlight: 145,000gns yearling; showed some promise with his keeping-on fourth of seven, albeit without landing a blow, in Doncaster contest (7f, good to firm; 11-2 shot); open to improvement.

comment: 42,000gns foal; by Study Of Man; Dewhurst entry suggests he's well regarded
spotlight: 42,000gns foal; by Study Of Man and first foal of unraced daughter of 12.5f Listed winning half-sister to two Group 1 scorers; Dewhurst entry suggests he's well regarded.

comment: 80,000gns yearling; by Without Parole; stable 3-22 with 2yos this year
spotlight: 21,000gns foal, 80,000gns yearling; Without Parole half-brother to an Italian 6f winner, out of maiden (RPR 66) half-sister to 6f 2yo scorer Elronaq; stable 3-22 with 2yos this year.

comment: Attractively bred newcomer, by Dubawi out of 2yo scorer whose siblings include Enable
spotlight: Juddmonte newcomer who is very attractively bred, being by Dubawi out of a Group-placed 1m AW 2yo scorer (RPR 101) whose siblings include Oaks/dual Arc winner Enable; interesting.

comment: Won first two before second on handicap debut; not disgraced in Group 1 since; big player
spotlight: Won at Ayr (5f, good) on sole 2yo start and made it 2-2 at Pontefract (6f, good) in April; met with defeat for the first time but improved again when second on 6f Windsor handicap debut (good to firm) at the beginning of June; bit better than result (not clear run over 2f out) when midfield in Group 1 Commonwealth Cup at Royal Ascot (6f, good to firm) since; his pedigree provides hope for this step up in trip; very interesting up against largely much more exposed opposition.

comment: Placed over C&D either side of Haydock win; handily drawn; should give good account
spotlight: In good form in his three outings this year, placing over C&D on good to firm (third to Rhythm Master latterly) either side of a 7f win at Haydock in July; handily drawn for a prominent racer and likely to give another good account.

comment: All three wins (including C&D) gained on going softer than good; likely needs rain
spotlight: Triple 7f winner on slow turf, including here; creditable fourth of 13 at Chester (7.5f, good) in May but his two efforts since have been no more than respectable; probably best to look elsewhere unless the ground goes on the soft side.

comment: Unexposed 3yo who proved himself at 7f last time and may not have reached his limit
spotlight: Lightly raced sort whose 6f form features two novice wins; beaten favourite in both handicaps but latter third over 7f at Newmarket (good to firm) was creditable and he remains unexposed after only five starts.

comment: C&D winner last autumn; went in again at Redcar in April but well held back here latest
spotlight: C&D winner last autumn and landed a ninth career success when accounting for eight rivals at Redcar (7f, good to firm) in April; bounced back from a couple of below-par efforts when chasing home Marhaba Ghaiyyath back at Redcar (1m, good to firm) in June but he was well behind Rhythm Master and Desert Falcon back here four weeks ago.

comment: Placed in Qatar in spring but held in Royal Ascot h'cap and French conditions race since
spotlight: Some useful placed efforts in Qatar in the spring but well held in Buckingham Palace at Royal Ascot on British return in June and last of seven in 1m Longchamp conditions event since; the cheekpieces he wore for one of those efforts in Qatar return; hard to be confident for yard which also runs Fine Interview.

comment: Below best since 7f Musselburgh win in spring
spotlight: Five-time winner at this trip, including at Musselburgh (good to soft) in April, but not at the same level in four outings since; only 1lb above mark he defied at Musselburgh but others arrive with more pressing claims.

comment: Effective on good but all three wins on soft; drawn wide; cheekpieces on; opposed for win
spotlight: Latest Glorious Goodwood fifth of 17 on good ground was creditable but all three wins have come on soft and he's probably opposable for win purposes here from an outside stall; wears first-time cheekpieces.

comment: Snapped losing run over C&D before third at Newmarket 14 days ago; ought to be competitive
spotlight: Snapped a losing run over C&D (good to firm; Desert Falcon third) at the beginning of the month and creditable third (Sterling Knight fourth) off this mark at Newmarket (1m, good to firm) 14 days ago; ought to be competitive again.
quotes: "[{\"date\": \"2022-06-25\", \"horse\": \"Rhythm Master\", \"horse_id\": \"hrs_21794619\", \"race\": \"Jenningsbet Handicap\", \"race_id\": \"rac_10581675\", \"course\": \"Newcastle (AW)\", \"course_id\": \"crs_35178\", \"distance_f\": \"7\", \"distance_y\": \"1554\", \"quote\": \"Rhythm Master has been a bit of a rogue. comment: Newcomer by Too Darn Hot out of Lancashire Oaks winner; stable also runs Accredit
spotlight: Newcomer by Too Darn Hot out of 1m-1m4f winner (including AW 2yo and Group 2 Lancashire Oaks; RPR 109); both parents were Gosden-trained; stable also runs Accredit; market informative.

comment: Bombproof gelding who is rarely far away in his races and each-way claims again
spotlight: Bombproof gelding who is rarely far away in his races and posted another solid effort off this mark when fourth (Rhythm Master third) of eight over 1m at Newmarket (good to firm) a fortnight ago; each-way claims under Billy Loughnane.

comment: Well treated on best sprint form but 7f seemed to stretch him latest and he's drawn widest
spotlight: Very well treated on best sprinting form but faded in the closing stages when tackling 7f for just a second time at Chester 26 days ago; has the outside stall so the negatives outweigh the positives.

comment: Ex-Richard Hannon; won a handicap in June 2024 but disappointing since; stable debut
spotlight: Ex-Richard Hannon; won a 7f Haydock handicap in June 2024; mainly disappointing since; best watched after a break on stable debut.

comment: Three wins here this year; below-par last time (April); may need the run after a break
spotlight: Has won three times here this year, last twice over 7f, the other at 1m; below-par when last seen in April and may need the run after 141-day break.

comment: Both wins have been over 6f here; fair efforts over 7f on turf last twice; should go well
spotlight: Both wins have been over 6f here, the latest in November last year; now 3lb lower and not disgraced over 7f on turf on last two starts; could go well.

comment: Won 6f handicap here in December; not as his best on last few starts; others look stronger
spotlight: Won a 6f handicap here last December; has run the occasional good race since, but not been at his best on last few starts and others look stronger.

comment: Ex-Irish; yet to find his form for this new yard and others look stronger
spotlight: Ex-Irish; yet to find his form for this new yard and others look stronger.

comment: Two C&D wins last December; not run since March; likely to be better for the run
spotlight: Won twice over C&D in December; mixed form after that (fair third to Cusack over C&D last time); off since March and likely to be better for the run.

comment: 7f AW maiden winner in Ireland; fine first run on turf for this yard (7f); should go well
spotlight: Won a Dundalk maiden when trained in Ireland; bought for 17,000gns in July and sound run off this mark when runner-up at Ayr on stable debut (7f, good); should go well.

comment: Ex-Irish; won 6f maiden last October; below-par this year; AW debut
spotlight: Ex-Irish; won a 6f Navan maiden last October (good to yielding); has yet to find his form for new yard; AW debut.
quotes: "[{\"date\": \"2024-10-09\", \"horse\": \"Sweet Thing\", \"horse_id\": \"hrs_45598637\", \"race\": \"Simonstown Maiden\", \"race_id\": \"rac_11421215\", \"course\": \"Navan\", \"course_id\": \"crs_5018\", \"distance_f\": \"6\", \"distance_y\": \"1280\", \"quote\": \"Unfortunately Sweet Thing had a wee setback earlier on in the year so it took a while to get her out, but we always liked her. comment: Five-time AW winner, including over 7f; good turf second two runs back; a possible
spotlight: Has won five times on the AW, including over 6f/7f here; good effort when second at Musselburgh two runs back (7f, good) but not so good over 6f at Hamilton last time; wouldn't rule out.

comment: 4-9 on AW including two wins over 6f here; has won over 7f; bit below best this year
spotlight: 4-9 on the AW, including two wins over 6f here; has won over 7f at Carlisle so stamina not an issue but not quite at his best on his two runs this year (both over 6f on turf).

owner: Pat Morris And Clear Cut Racing
comment: Three wins here, two over 7f; not at his best last three runs (after a break latest)
spotlight: Three wins have been over 7f/1m here, latest off 1lb lower in January; not at his best on last three runs, including after a break last time; other preferred.
quotes: "[{\"date\": \"2023-10-09\", \"horse\": \"Tasever\", \"horse_id\": \"hrs_30765105\", \"race\": \"Leslie Burton (Fisher) Handicap\", \"race_id\": \"rac_11043253\", \"course\": \"Pontefract\", \"course_id\": \"crs_1196\", \"distance_f\": \"8\", \"distance_y\": \"1766\", \"quote\": \"Tasever ran a blinder too and I hope he'll get his win soon - Tim Easterby, trainer.\"}]"

comment: Two best runs have been here; not quite at his best last three starts; wouldn't rule out
spotlight: Two best runs have been over 7f/1m here; not quite in top form on last three starts, including on turf debut after a break last time; wouldn't rule out.

comment: Has won three times over C&D, latest in February; turf winner in July but below-par since
spotlight: Has won three times over C&D, the latest off a 6lb lower mark in February; won again at Thirsk in July (7f, good; rated 2lb lower than here) but below-par since.

comment: Not at his best since winning at Chelmsford in early July (7f); needs to bounce back
spotlight: Not at his best since winning at Chelmsford in early July (7f, standard to slow); needs to bounce back.

comment: 1m winner in June; below best latest; has to prove she's still effective over this trip
spotlight: Six wins at 1m3f down to 1m, most recently over the latter trip at Chepstow (soft) in June; below best there latest, though, and has to prove she's still effective over this sort of trip.

comment: Five AW wins at 7f and 1m; 0-3 on turf but creditable latest; of interest
spotlight: All five wins on AW, at 7f and 1m, and he's run only three times on turf, but he did well in the circumstances (1m, good to firm; blindfold removed late; first time in these aids) when runner-up at Newmarket two weeks ago; up 2lb but of interest; unraced on slower than good.

comment: Won two of last three AW runs; high in weights now back on turf but rain helpful
spotlight: Has won two of her last three AW starts, at 7f and 1m, but her turf mark has risen in tandem and she has something to prove back on grass, having been soundly beaten at Brighton on latest attempt in May (won on soft there in 2024); rain helpful, though.
quotes: "[{\"date\": \"2023-01-04\", \"horse\": \"Capuchinero\", \"horse_id\": \"hrs_27166279\", \"race\": \"Book Online At dundalkstadium.com Claiming Race\", \"race_id\": \"rac_10791456\", \"course\": \"Dundalk (AW)\", \"course_id\": \"crs_29588\", \"distance_f\": \"7\", \"distance_y\": \"1540\", \"quote\": \"Capuchinero is genuine and tough. comment: Mostly raced at sprint trips but C&D winner last week; still well treated despite penalty
spotlight: Has won on good ground but suited by slower; most racing over sprint trips but she's broadened her horizons over 7f of late and found plenty when winning over C&D last week, idling in front; 1lb badly in under penalty but she won off a higher mark than today's in 2024; good chance.

comment: AW winner at 7f in March; still in form but below best latest; worth a look back on turf
spotlight: Some good AW runs in the spring, winning over 7f at Kempton, and he still looked in form at Southwell in July; made no impact when down in grade at Wolverhampton recently but still worth a look back on turf.

comment: Three 7f wins on AW; 0-3 on turf and not in much form of late; cheekpieces on
spotlight: Three 7f wins on Kempton AW; down weights but he's 0-3 on turf and not in much form in recent times, most recently at Kempton when back from another break for new yard; unconvincing with cheekpieces fitted.

comment: Stayed on well for third on 7f Newcastle debut, suggesting 1m will suit; considered
spotlight: 11-1, stayed on well for third of ten on debut at Newcastle (7f, AW) five weeks ago; this well-bred Saxon Warrior colt is open to improvement now up in trip and could have a big part to play.

comment: 7f nursery win last August but has lost her way since
spotlight: Won a 7f Carlisle nursery (soft) last August but has lost her way since, faring little better back from wind surgery at Carlisle seven weeks ago; falling in the weights but need to see more.

comment: 33-1 and no obvious short-term promise on 7f Goodwood debut four weeks ago
spotlight: Half-sister to five winners but 33-1 and no obvious short-term promise on 7f Goodwood debut (heavy) four weeks ago.

comment: Reached frame in all handicaps for Andrew Balding; headgear off on first run for new yard
spotlight: Reached the frame on all six handicap starts at up to 1m2f for Andrew Balding, although he did look awkward under pressure on occasions; changed hands for 8,000gns in July; headgear worn on last four runs is left off starting out for new yard.

comment: Came from last to first at Beverley last month; fourth at Ayr since; enters the reckoning
spotlight: Came with a strong run from the rear to get off the mark at Beverley (extended 7f, soft) last month, his third start for Ruth Carr;  raced keenly and couldn't sustain his effort late on when fourth in 1m classified event at Ayr three weeks later; that probably shouldn't be taken to suggest he can't make an impact from his new mark.

comment: Placed twice around 1m in July but ran poorly latest, taking record to 0-13
spotlight: Placed twice around 1m in July but ran poorly at Doncaster last time, taking his record to 0-13; bounce back needed under Jude Fernandes, who had his first winner at Goodwood last week.

owner: Sheikh Hamdan bin Mohammed Al Maktoum
comment: Beaten just under 9l on recent Salisbury debut but should progress
spotlight: Nathaniel filly who was beaten just under 9l when fifth of six on 1m Salisbury debut (good to firm) 15 days ago; should progress.

comment: Showed ability when fourth on recent Beverley debut but he was beaten 11l
spotlight: Showed ability on recent Beverley debut over an extended 7f but he was beaten 11l and will need to find a chunk of improvement to go close.

comment: Started out for this yard with encouraging efforts but below par last twice
spotlight: Started out for this yard with some quite encouraging efforts but below par on his last two outings; the first-time cheekpieces and tongue-tie he wore last time are quickly discarded.

comment: Second at Carlisle (7f) in June but struggled since; had wind surgery (also tongue-tied)
spotlight: Only just lost out at Carlisle (7f, soft) in June but hasn't done so well in three outings over 7f/6f since; up in trip on return from  wind surgery with a tongue-tie also added.

comment: Running to consistent level in 2025 and this 10yo should be in the thick of things again
spotlight: Running to a consistent level in 2025, including third of six at Redcar (1m2f, good to firm) last Saturday; this veteran should be in the thick of the action once more.

comment: Hinted at ability on York debut but not enough to suggest he's likely to strike here
spotlight: 50-1, hinted at ability when eighth of 16 on 7f York debut five weeks ago but not enough to suggest he's likely to strike here.

comment: Consistent but latest 6l second shows she's vulnerable to a promising sort; headgear on
spotlight: Consistency hard to knock with runner-up finishes on all five starts but no match for a promising newcomer at Beverley (7.5f, good to firm) 16 days ago and there might another one in this line-up; wears first-time cheekpieces.

comment: Down the field in two AW outings; gelded ahead of turf debut
spotlight: Down the field in two AW outings at Newcastle in recent weeks; gelded ahead of this switch to turf; probably more one for handicaps after this.

comment: Group entries ambitious but has shown ability both starts, latterly third over 7f on AW
spotlight: Group entries look ambitious but she has shown ability on both starts, latterly third of nine over 7f at Kempton; faded in the closing stages on that occasion so it remains to be seen if the step up to 1m proves beneficial.

comment: Cost 775,000gns as a yearling and is entered in Group 1 Fillies' Mile; obvious appeal
spotlight: 775,000gns daughter of Night Of Thunder and the second foal of a 1m6f Group 3 winner (RPR 107); entered in the Group 1 Fillies' Mile; very interesting newcomer for whom market confidence would likely prove significant.

comment: Form of 7f Brighton second franked but he'll need to settle better now moving up to 1m
spotlight: Has run twice over 7f on good to firm, stepping up a little on his debut when second at Brighton 22 days ago; the winner gave the form a bit of a boost when running well under a penalty at Goodwood last weekend but this step up to 1m is slight worry given he's pulled hard on both starts.

comment: Bred to have a future but it's likely best to look elsewhere this time
spotlight: 12,000gns half-brother to five winners, including Carpathian (German 1m7f/2m3f Listed; RPR 103), Yellow Tiger (1m3f Flat, 87; 2m hurdle) and Payment Plan (2m AW; 66); bred to have a future but it's likely best to look elsewhere this time.

comment: Likely outsider on debut
spotlight: By Expert Eye and the third foal of an unraced sister to 5f/6f winner Boundary Lane; has been gelded; likely outsider on debut.

comment: Three of five AW wins under Ellie Mayo; third on turf latest but Sandret was over 5l ahead
spotlight: All five wins on AW, with the latest three coming under Ellie Mayo (5f-1m); led for a long way but faded into third behind Sandret at Redcar (1m, good) last month; enjoys a 6lb pull in the weights with that one now but it may not be enough.

comment: Three 7f wins this summer; another good effort when second last week; should go well
spotlight: Three 7f turf wins (good/good to firm) in June/July; a couple of below-par effort followed but she produced a career-best when second of ten over 7f at Catterick (good to firm) off this mark 11 days ago; has the done the majority of her racing in the last couple of years over 7f but had winning form over further earlier in her career; should go well.

comment: No impact in four runs for Kevin Frost, including tailed off on 1m handicap debut
spotlight: Modest form at best in four outings for Kevin Frost, including tailed off on 1m handicap debut in June; stable has enjoyed success with new recruits under both codes this summer but can still only watch.

owner: D Bishop P Robinson S Bland T Coyle
comment: Related to winners but best watched on debut unless betting hints otherwise

spotlight: Unseated on hurdles debut before decent fourth at Roscommon; followed that with a 3.75l second at Perth most recently; she is getting to grips with hurdling but may find one or two better than her.

comment: Improved effort on second hurdles start; can improve jumping still and no penalty
spotlight: 72 rated maiden on the Flat after six starts, with some placed form; improved over Killarney hurdles debut at Ballinrobe last time to finish third (2m, good), with Hopes Are High in front of him that day but now that rival carries a penalty; still room for improvement in the jumping department; chance.

comment: Unplaced in 15 starts under rules inc' sole hurdles run last time; big improvement needed
spotlight: Unplaced in 15 starts under rules, including sole attempt over hurdles at Wexford last time when a 13.5l sixth (2m1f, good); big improvement needed

comment: 15l behind on hurdles debut last month; change of stable needs to bring big improvement
spotlight: AW winner in December and a couple of placed finishes on Flat; 15l behind the winner at Tipperary last month on hurdles debut; switch of stable would need to bring big improvement.

comment: Undistinguished Flat form but wide margin juvenile hurdle winner; others preferred
spotlight: Undistinguished Flat form but was a wide margin winner of a juvenile hurdle at Market Rasen on her only try over obstacles (2m, good), hard to know if she beat very much there; switched to current yard for Galway Flat run last month where she was tailed off; return to hurdles a positive but others preferred.

comment: 70 rated on the Flat with some okay runs; not ruled out if taking to hurdles
spotlight: 70 rated on the Flat after six runs, the best of those being a 0.5l third at Limerick in June for Jessica Harrington(1m3f, good); switched to current stable at Naas last time with a respectable fourth (1m2f, good to yielding); not ruled out if taking to this new discipline.

comment: Flat maiden winner tries hurdling now and is entitled to respect given connections
spotlight: Winner of a Tipperary Flat maiden on the third attempt (1m4f, yielding); tries hurdling now on return from a 127-day absence; entitled to respect given connections.

comment: Four-time hurdle winner, latest win at Killarney last month; well beaten on Flat latest
spotlight: Four-time winner over hurdles; latest win came at Killarney last month (2m4f, yielding to soft); 12.5l behind at Kilbeggan following that off 7lb higher mark and was well beaten on the Flat at Tramore most recently (2m, good to yielding); can get involved on best form.

spotlight: Only hints of ability in three Flat maidens but ran out a surprise winner on hurdling debut at Killarney last time (2m1f, yielding to soft); there didn't appear to be a fluke about the result that day, so one for the shortlist.

comment: Off the mark immediately over hurdles at Ballinrobe last time; must shoulder a penalty
spotlight: 0-5 on the Flat but off the mark immediately over hurdles at Ballinrobe last time (2m, good); had Cinammon Coco behind him on that occasion off level weights but now must shoulder a penalty.

owner: Barrow Vale Syndicate/A D Mullins/Ms Margaret Mullins
comment: Not great form on the Flat and 16l behind Something Noble on hurdles bow last time
spotlight: Not much to get excited about in five Flat runs and was 16l behind Something Noble on his hurdling bow at Killarney last month (2m1f, yielding to soft); hard to see him featuring.

comment: Wore retained tongue-tie for good second at Cork last time; up just 1lb, shortlisted
spotlight: Unseated early on handicap debut at Kilbeggan when fancied; unplaced favourite in maiden back there on penultimate; wore first-time tongue tie (retained) for good second at Cork last time (2m1f, good); raised just 1lb now and one for the shortlist

comment: Decent efforts in five maiden hurdles and fell latest when looked in command; chance
spotlight: Decent efforts in five maiden hurdles; clear second to a next-time-out winner at Bangor in June (2m, good), before falling at two out back at that track latest (2m3f, good) when she looked like she would take some beating; rated 8lb inferior to Astelia but not discounted.

comment: Arrested decline with 40-1 second at Uttoxeter last month; still very well handicapped
spotlight: Generally very disappointing since C&D (good) win off 24lb higher in spring 2024 but arrested his decline with 40-1 second at Uttoxeter (2m, good) last month and should cope if the ground softens here.

comment: One Flat run in Germany in 2024 was poor; joined a good yard to go hurdling
spotlight: Showed nothing in one Flat run in Germany (1m) in July 2024 but she's joined a respected yard since then; well worth a market check, especially with the stable also running Galactique.

comment: All four Flat runs for new stable this year have been disappointing; back hurdling today
spotlight: Went close over hurdles for David Bridgwater at Newton Abbot (2m2f, good) last summer but his four Flat runs for James Owen this year have all been disappointing and it's hard to know what to expect from him here.

comment: Not beaten far when midfield on last month's handicap debut but improvement is needed
spotlight: 0-9 on the Flat and 0-4 over hurdles; not beaten far when seventh of 15 on handicap hurdle debut at Worcester (2m, good) last month but improvement is required here.

comment: Dual C&D winner but not since December 2022, and is very inconsistent nowadays
spotlight: Dual C&D winner (soft/good) but not since December 2022, and is very inconsistent nowadays; tailed off at Stratford on latest outing in early July; 1lb wrong today; others have more pressing claims.

owner: Alan Jamieson Site Services & G L Moore
comment: Yet to build upon her promising bumper debut but is open to improvement now handicapping
spotlight: Yet to build upon last year's promising bumper debut (good to soft) and was well held when third in 2m3f novice here (good) in June but makes her handicap debut in a low-grade event and is open to improvement.

comment: Veteran; returned from 640-day absence with quiet run in February; off for 206 days since
spotlight: Veteran who returned from 640-day absence with a down-the-field run in February and has been absent for another seven months since; very well handicapped on old form and will be favoured by the forecast rain but is tricky to weigh up at present.

comment: Took step forward when third at Sedgefield in March; a possible if tuned up after break
spotlight: Fair on the Flat at his best; generally very disappointing over hurdles but his third of five at Sedgefield (2m4f, good) in March was a big step forward; drops back in trip with cheekpieces refitted here; could have a say if tuned up after 171-day break.

comment: Ran poorly last time but was clear second to progressive rival on stable debut in June
spotlight: Ex-Irish 8yo; ran poorly at Uttoxeter last month and is now 0-21 over hurdles but was clear second to a progressive rival on stable debut at Worcester (2m, good to soft) two starts ago and has good claims if judged on that.

comment: Battled well for narrow win in February but made low-key reappearance last month
spotlight: Battled on well for narrow win at Plumpton (2m, soft) in February but returned from break with low-key run last month and probably needs to rebound with a career-best performance here.

comment: Pretty good third on handicap debut in June but two disappointing runs have followed
spotlight: Ran well for a long way when third of seven on handicap debut at Ffos Las (2m, good to soft) in June but two disappointing runs have followed (2m5f/2m) and he comes here with something to prove.

comment: In high-profile colours but 0-7 on the Flat and ended up with a BHA mark in the low 60s
spotlight: In high-profile colours but 0-7 on the Flat and ended up with a BHA mark in the low 60s; should stay okay over hurdles as latest second at Wolverhampton was over 1m4f, albeit in a field of four (in first-time cheekpieces).

comment: Eight runs on the Flat, winning a 1m4f AW handicap in April; mixed since
spotlight: Eight runs on the Flat, winning a 1m4f AW handicap in April; mixed since but won't fail through a lack of stamina on this hurdling debut.

comment: Finished a 23l last of the seven runners in a 1m6f maiden at Goodwood; hard to assess
spotlight: Finished a 23l last of the seven runners in a 1m6f maiden at Goodwood; hard to assess.

comment: 1m AW winner for Ralph Beckett in March; finished last in a 1m handicap on yard debut
spotlight: 1m AW winner for Ralph Beckett in March, after which he was well held in a novice; finished last in a 1m AW handicap on debut for this yard and hard to be confident after that.

comment: His run behind Dignam at Uttoxeter entitles him to be on the premises with Lord
spotlight: Regressed on the Flat but his run behind Dignam at Uttoxeter entitles him to be on the premises with Lord; solid chance.

comment: 11-race Flat maiden and was 33-1 when departing early on hurdling debut at Stratford
spotlight: Inferior to some of these on the Flat as an 11-race maiden and was 33-1 when departing early on hurdling debut at Stratford.

comment: Flat ability in Germany and bumped into the smart Dignam on hurdling debut at Newton Abbot
spotlight: Showed ability in two Flat runs when trained in Germany and bumped into the smart Dignam on hurdling debut at Newton Abbot; remains to be seen what he achieved but looks the most likely winner of this.

comment: Four runs for Ralph Beckett, posting RPRs in the 70s in two of those so has ability
spotlight: Four runs for Ralph Beckett, posting RPRs in the 70s in two of those so has ability; joined this yard for 22,000gns and could be a hurdler.

comment: Makes handicap debut after a layoff but still worth a check in the market
spotlight: Low-grade Flat winner last summer; showed only minor promise against own sex in three juvenile/maiden hurdles last autumn and makes handicap hurdle debut after ten-month absence but still worth a check in the market.

comment: Disappointing favourite on last month's stable debut but can come good for new yard soon
spotlight: Three-time chase winner when trained by James Ewart (2m-2m4f, good-soft); disappointing favourite when only fourth of five on last month's stable debut at Uttoxeter (2m, good) but remains on a workable mark and it won't be a surprise if he comes good for Olly Murphy soon.

owner: Awr Consultancy Ltd & The Folly Partners
comment: Not at best on latest outing but is 2-4 since switched to fences this season; respected
spotlight: 2-4 since switched to fences this season; not at best when well-held third at Stratford (2m3f, good) last month but should cope if the ground softens here and remains of interest.

comment: C&D winnerr; ran well after a layoff last summer; returns from another absence today
spotlight: Scored over C&D (good) in October 2023 and returned from 226-day absence with creditable third at Worcester (2m4f, good) last summer; major player if in similar form after an even longer layoff here; handles good to soft ground; unproven on anything slower.

comment: In poor form on the Flat since last summer and has too much to prove on chasing debut
spotlight: Not seen under jumps rules since pulled up in soft-ground handicap hurdle in April 2023 and has been in poor form on the Flat since last summer; has too much to prove on chasing debut; refitted cheekpieces replace visor.

owner: Noel Fehily Racing Syndicate - Claim Du
comment: Respectable third on last month's handicap hurdle debut; quickly switched to chasing
spotlight: Bumper/novice hurdle winner this spring; just a respectable third on last month's handicap hurdle debut at Stratford (2m2f, good) but Dan Skelton is evidently very keen to switch this slow-ground Irish point runner-up to chasing.

comment: Ran quite well over fences in May but well beaten over hurdles since; not convincing
spotlight: Fell in both her chases last season; seemed to be getting her act together over fences when third of six at Stratford (2m1f, good) in May but was well beaten over hurdles there last month; others in this line-up have more persuasive profiles.

comment: Makes handicap debut from a lowly mark but still needs significant improvement
spotlight: Makes handicap debut from a lowly mark but showed no significant promise in his three qualifying races in February/March (2m-2m4f); sports first-time cheekpieces; improvement required.

comment: 0-3 over hurdles for three different stables; improvement possible in handicaps
spotlight: 0-3 over hurdles for three different stables; not beaten far when seventh of eight at Uttoxeter (2m, good) on last month's debut for Olly Murphy and now moves back up in trip for first handicap; improvement possible.

comment: 0-13 over hurdles but ran well on both starts this season and rain will aid his cause
spotlight: 0-13 over hurdles but went down fighting when close second at Southwell (2m4f, good) in May and again ran well at Stratford (2m6f, good to firm) last month; well suited by ground slower than good; high on the list.

comment: Ran well when third at Stratford last month but 0-19 over hurdles now; others preferred
spotlight: Ran well when third at Stratford (2m2f, good) last month but was safely held in the end and is now 0-19 over hurdles; handles good to soft ground but probably doesn't want soft; others appeal more.

comment: Pulled up when 33-1 for handicap debut one year ago; not seen again since
spotlight: With a good stable and still very lightly raced but was pulled up when 33-1 for handicap debut here (2m5f, good) one year ago and has not raced again since; had wind op last September.

comment: 0-8 over hurdles but recent handicap form has been respectable; considered each-way
spotlight: 0-8 over hurdles but recent handicap form (2m1f-2m4f) has been very respectable and he seems versatile ground-wise; considered each-way.

comment: Pulled-up outsider on last month's stable debut; difficult to enthuse over
spotlight: 0-13 over hurdles for Gavin Cromwell in Ireland and, following a one-year absence, was a pulled-up outsider for new stable last month.

comment: Yet to show any worthwhile form after six hurdling starts and is 8lb wrong today
spotlight: Yet to show any worthwhile form after six hurdling starts and competes from 8lb out of the handicap here.

comment: Close third off this mark in June; moves up from 2m today; forecast rain a worry
spotlight: 0-5 over hurdles but was very close third off today's mark at Worcester (2m, good) in June and also ran well in defeat on the Flat last month; tries a new trip today; would probably prefer the ground to remain good.

comment: Multiple AW winner for this stable since December; may still have potential over hurdles
spotlight: Multiple AW winner for current stable since December and comfortably made winning handicap hurdle debut in four-runner race at Southwell (2m, good) in June; shade disappointing on both subsequent hurdling starts but may still have potential over jumps and is likely to be suited by today's move up in trip; seems quite versatile ground-wise.

comment: Pulled up on both starts for current stable; returns from 196-day absence here
spotlight: Not fully exposed after only seven starts but was pulled up on consecutive appearances for this new stable in February (2m4f/2m7f) and returns from 196-day break with lots to prove.

comment: Hard to predict nowadays but looked in good nick when winning at Newton Abbot in June
spotlight: Hard to predict nowadays but looked in good nick when scoring at Newton Abbot (2m2f, good) on penultimate hurdle run and can be excused recent Flat defeat; unproven on soft ground but can cope with good to soft; a possible.

comment: Well held on both recent Flat starts but remains very unexposed over jumps
spotlight: Won on the Flat in France last year and subsequently showed hurdling ability against own age-group in Britain; returned from layoff with two very underwhelming Flat runs this summer but remains very unexposed over jumps.

comment: Looked held when falling last month, on first appearance for 1045 days
spotlight: Useful on the Flat in his prime and showed some hurdling promise in 2022; looked held before falling at Worcester last month, his first run for 1045 days, and current ability remains hard to gauge; cheekpieces added.

comment: Makes chase debut after three good efforts in handicap hurdles at this track
spotlight: Fine from 2m to 3m; makes chase debut after three good efforts in handicap hurdles at this track and this 6yo could be open to improvement.

comment: Beat You Oughta Know here on chase debut; placed over hurdles since then
spotlight: Inferior hurdler to You Oughta Know but he beat the Mullins horse fair and square on his chase debut here before finishing a close third back here in a handicap hurdle; should be on the premises.

spotlight: Only 1-18 over hurdles but made a pleasing chase debut when a 2l fourth at Tramore (1m7f handicap); was running on so should stay this far; may need good ground so watch the weather.

owner: Sussex By The Sea Syndicate/David L'Estrange
comment: Second over hurdles last time and no surprise should she raise her game over fences
spotlight: Tramore maiden hurdle winner, her sole success; had become disappointing but her recent second in a 2m4f handicap hurdle here was a step in the right direction and the dam is from a very good jumping family; this mare has the scope for fences.

comment: Remains a maiden over jumps and was well behind Doyen Magic last time
spotlight: Three-time Flat winner but remains a maiden over jumps and was well behind Doyen Magic last time in a 2m4f handicap chase.

comment: Placed over hurdles; competitive mark and would have a chance if taking to fences
spotlight: Is 0-12 over hurdles but placed again last time at Roscommon in a 3m handicap; on a competitive mark and could have a role to play if taking to fences.

comment: Comfortable Kilbeggan winner but tried to run out when unseating earlier this week
spotlight: Only her second run for this yard and debut over fences when winning comfortably at Kilbeggan (2m4f, good to yielding); worryingly, she tried to run out when unseating at Downpatrick on Monday when 9-2 to defy this 6lb higher mark.

comment: Only his second run over fences when a front-running third over C&D
spotlight: Sligo maiden hurdle winner; a half-brother to Grand National winner Corach Rambler and only his second run over fences when a front-running third over C&D (handicap) three weeks ago; jumped well and can improve some more.

comment: Beaten fair and square by War Correspondent last time but he does have a 4lb pull
spotlight: Smart bumper/hurdle form and looking every bit as good over fences despite coming up shy when a shade of odds-on the last twice (2m4f/2m), latterly here behind War Correspondent; had no excuses that day but he's 4lb better off with the winner.

spotlight: Rain welcomed; his form over hurdles and fences has an uneven look to it but he's capable on his day, having won a beginners' chase in 2023 and this year finishing first and second in big-field handicap hurdles; hard to discount.

spotlight: Flat/hurdle winner; made it 0-3 over fences when tailed off over 2m here a month ago and that was after some modest runs on the Flat and over hurdles.

comment: Second in a claiming hurdle on Wednesday; faces a tough task on these terms
spotlight: Ran okay to be third in a novice handicap chase at Perth before finishing runner-up in a claiming hurdle at Bellewstown on Wednesday; dual chase winner but penalised accordingly and up against it on these terms.

comment: C&D winner but 25-1 for a Grade 3 at Galway when well behind Intellotto
spotlight: A 126-rated hurdler; narrowly made a winning start as a chaser over C&D before struggling in a Grade 3 at Galway when 25-1; finished well behind Intellotto that day.

comment: Beaten a long way in a bumper and two maiden hurdles; look elsewhere
spotlight: Beaten a long way in a bumper and two maiden hurdles; look elsewhere.

owner: F W Healy & Philip Bowe & Ms Margaret Mullins
comment: Well beaten in bumpers at Cork and Galway; likely capable of better in time

spotlight: Descending mark but has to show more than previous three handicap attempts.

comment: Listowel winner last year; returns from almost a year off so probably best watched

spotlight: Only beaten about 3l when fourth at Worcester (2m7f, good) six weeks ago and has now made the frame in four of his last five chases (unseated rider in the other); still on a workable mark and rain won't bother him; swaps usual cheekpieces for first-time visor today.

comment: Back under rules with two convincing 2m4f wins this season; tries a new trip today
spotlight: Easily won two points in May (both 3m, good) and returned to racing under rules with convincing chase wins at Worcester and Uttoxeter (both 2m4f, good) in June/July; untested beyond 3m but ought to cope if the ground softens here and needs to be taken very seriously in current mood.

comment: Didn't fire last month but has generally done well for new stable this season; respected
spotlight: Scored at Uttoxeter (3m, good) in May, his second start for James Owen, and ran big race when clear second to thriving opponent at Cartmel (3m1f, soft) in June; needs to bounce back from last month's duff effort at Market Rasen but still features prominently in calculations.

comment: Battled on to snatch modest third on final Irish start; makes stable debut here
spotlight: 0-12 under all codes when based in Ireland; battled on well to snatch modest third of 15 at Wexford (3m1f, good) last month and is still unexposed over fences but others have more pressing claims here; blinkers removed for this stable debut.
